news.title: Outlook stable for real estate this fiscal
news.para: Residential supply to match demand; leasing momentum in commercial space to continue

news.title: IndoSpace plans to invest Rs 4,500 crore in logistics and warehouse parks in Tamil Nadu
news.para: IndoSpace's total equity committed to the state as on date stands at USD 380 million, and the facilities offer a potential chargeable area of 15.4 million sq ft.

news.title: CBRE to manage NetApp's 1.07 million sq ft office spaces
news.para: The portfolio consists of NetApp’s campus in Bengaluru and sales offices in Bengaluru, Mumbai and New Delhi.

news.title: PE investment in real estate touch $3.9 billion in January-September 2024: Report
news.para: The PE inflows were at $2.2 billion (Rs 186 billion) in Q3 2024. The inflows were $6.7 billion in 2019, $6.6 billion in 2020, $3.4 billion in 2021, $3.4 billion in 2022, and $3.9 billion in 2023.

news.title: Ashiana Housing's sales bookings touch Rs 673 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Tuesday, Ashiana Housing reported that its sales bookings stood at Rs 673.05 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal as against Rs 325.60 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Keystone Realtors sales bookings surge to Rs 700 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Keystone Realtors reported pre-sales of Rs 700 crore in the second quarter of the 2024-25 fiscal as compared to Rs 306 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Telangana government reveals 171 water bodies within ORR lost in 10 years
news.para: ​​Though the lakes were spread over 3,586.12 acres in 2014, when the new state was formed, squatters have encroached upon over 386 acres, worth several thousands of crores.

news.title: Manual khata remains relevant: Tushar Giri Nath, BBMP chief
news.para: In an interview, the Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) Chief Commissioner Tushar Giri Nath discusses the current efforts, future plans, and actions being taken to address these issues and improve conditions for the city’s residents.

news.title: TIDCO to allot land parcels in Sulur from next month
news.para: TIDCO plans to allot parcels of land to various companies to set up their manufacturing units at the Aerospace and Defence (A&D) Park at Varapatti in Sulur taluk in the district from next month.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises Rs 2,000 crore debt
news.para: The raised capital includes NCD issuance of Rs 900 crore of Embassy REIT Series XI NCDs 2024 with effective interest rate of 7.87% and Rs 1,100 crore of term loans from public sector undertakings (PSU) & MNC banks at ~8% floating coupon.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board resumes Wednesday e-auctions
news.para: Officials said that from now on, the Wednesday e-auction will take place every Wednesday, while the RHB will announce auctions for premium properties at certain intervals.

news.title: Trichy: Tidel Park launches Rs 315.2 crore tender for new IT Park
news.para: This project will add 5.5 lakh square feet of IT and ITES office space, tripling the city's existing infrastructure. Private developers are also planning to contribute another 6 lakh square feet of office space in response to growing demand from investors drawn to Trichy's low operational costs and access to the talent pool.

news.title: Over 35 lakh houses made in Uttar Pradesh under PMAY-Gramin
news.para: The official further said against the target of constructing 2.57 lakh houses from 2018-19 to 2023-24, work on 2.52 lakh houses has been completed, and 3,929 houses are under construction.

news.title: Delhi environment minister fines construction firm for violating anti-dust guidelines
news.para: "The construction site is not following the regulations, so the government has issued a notice to the company. Due to this violation, the DPCC (Delhi Pollution Control Committee) has imposed a fine of Rs 5 lakh on the company," the minister told reporters.

news.title: Paint wars: Dulux shade card may be part of a merged palette
news.para: Akzo Nobel India has informed that its Dutch parent Akzo Nobel NV is conducting a strategic review of its portfolio to redeploy capital towards growing its core coatings businesses. The initial focus will be on its decorative paints business in South Asia and various strategic options will be explored ranging from partnerships or joint ventures through to mergers or divestments.

news.title: Property registrations in Karnataka plunge 95% due to e-khata glitches
news.para: In the first two quarters of this fiscal, property registrations increased by 5% over last year, raking in Rs 11,550 crore, up from Rs 9,419 crore in the same period last year.

news.title: Housing finance companies propose increasing guarantee cover for home loans up to Rs 25 lakh
news.para: HFCs have sought a guarantee cover of up to 75% on a ₹25 lakh home loan. The current scheme, which has a budgetary allocation of ₹550 crores, provides up to 90% guarantee for home loans up to ₹2 lakhs, and up to 85% for loan amounts of ₹2-5 lakh.

news.title: Maharashtra government may allot 100 acres in Madh Island for Dharavi redevelopment project
news.para: ​​A portion of the land will be demarcated for other applicants, including singer Kailash Kher's singing academy, Aditya Birla group's proposal for a hospital, an MLA housing society, and a temple trust. The proposal is expected to be presented at the next meeting of the state cabinet.

news.title: Gujarat RERA mandates QR codes in real estate advertisement
news.para: It recently issued a circular mandating the inclusion of Quick Response (QR) code in all advertisements, brochures and prospectuses published or distributed by real estate developers about a project.
